berg-tm%20is%20synonymous%20with%20the%20free%20distribution%20of%20electronic%20works%20in%20formats%20readable%20by%20the%20widest%20variety%20of%20computers%20including%20obsolete%2C%20old%2C%20middle-aged%20and%20new%20computers.%20It%20exists%20because%20of%20the%20efforts%20of%20hundreds%20of%20volunteers%20and%20donations%20from%20people%20in%20all%20walks%20of%20life.%20Volunteers%20and%20financial%20support%20to%20provide%20volunteers%20with%20the%20assistance%20they%20need%2C%20is%20critical%20to%20reaching%20Project%20Gutenberg-tm%26%2339%3Bs%20goals%20and%20ensuring%20that%20the%20Project%20Gutenberg-tm%20collection%20will%20remain%20freely%20available%20for%20generations%20to%20come.%20In%202001%2C%20the%20Project%20Gutenberg%20Literary%20Archive%20Foundation%20was%20created%20to%20provide%20a%20secure%20and%20permanent%20future%20for%20Project%20Gutenberg-tm%20and%20future%20generations.%20To%20learn%20more%20about%20the%20Project%20Gutenberg%20Literary%20Archive%20Foundation%20and%20how%20your%20efforts%20and%20donations%20can%20help%2C%20see%20Sections%203%20and%204%20and%20the%20Foundation%20web%20page%20at%20http%3A%2F%2Fwww.pglaf.org.%20Section%203.%20Information%20about%20the%20Project%20Gutenberg%20Literary%20Archive%20Foundation%20The%20Project%20Gutenberg%20Literary%20Archive%20Foundation%20is%20a%20non%20profit%20501(c)(3)%20educational%20corporation%20organized%20under%20the%20laws%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Mississippi%20and%20granted%20tax%20exempt%20status%20by%20the%20Internal%20Revenue%20Service.%20The%20Foundation%26%2339%3Bs%20EIN%20or%20federal%20tax%20identification%20number%20is%2064-6221541.%20Its%20501(c)(3)%20letter%20is%20posted%20at%20http%3A%2F%2Fpglaf.org%2Ffundraising.%20Contributions%20to%20the%20Project%20Gutenberg%20Literary%20Archive%20Foundation%20are%20tax%20deductible%20to%20the%20full%20extent%20permitted%20by%20U.S.%20federal%20laws%20and%20your%20state%26%2339%3Bs%20laws.%20The%20Foundation%26%2339%3Bs%20principal%